%20at%20home.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EOrdering%20a%20braised%20dish%20or%20meal%20that%20takes%20a%20long%20time%20to%20make%20is%20a%20smart%20way%20to%20spend%20your%20money.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20margherita%20pizza%20and%20cacio%20e%20pepe%20are%20usually%20way%20overpriced%20and%20not%20a%20great%20value.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20Italian%20restaurants%20serve%20up%20tasty%20classics%2C%20but%20not%20everything%20on%20the%20menu%20is%20equal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20consulted%20with%20real%20chefs%20to%20pinpoint%20which%20common%20Italian-restaurant%20offerings%20are%20worthy%20of%20space%20on%20your%20plate%20and%20which%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-dishes-you-should-always-cook-at-home-2019-2%5C%22%3Ebetter%20prepared%20at%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20or%20skipped%20altogether%20because%20they're%20a%20bad%20value.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20to%20order%20and%20what%20to%20avoid%20next%20time%20you%20visit%20an%20Italian%20eatery.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAn%20Italian%20restaurant%20is%20the%20ideal%20place%20to%20get%20lasagna.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221881%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lasagna%20in%20white%20pan%20on%20plate%20at%20restaurant%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e85377bf0250c21493b6da%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221410%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELasagna%20can%20be%20time-consuming%20to%20make%20at%20home.%3Cp%3EIrina%20Marwan%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPersonal%20chef%20and%20nutritionist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.viaskitchen.com%2F%5C%22%3EMelissa%20Eboli%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20lasagna%20is%20an%20Italian%20staple%2C%20but%20it%20can%20be%20a%20real%20pain%20to%20make%20at%20home%20since%20it's%20a%20layered%20dish%20made%20with%20strata%20of%20flat%20pasta%20and%20fillings%20such%20as%20meat%2C%20vegetables%2C%20and%20cheese.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLasagna%20is%20actually%20a%20very%20time-consuming%20and%20labor-intensive%20dish%20to%20make%20by%20yourself.%20Enjoy%20someone%20else's%20preparation%20of%20it%20at%20a%20restaurant%2C%20as%20a%20good%20lasagna%20is%20worth%20spending%20money%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Eboli%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20some%20more%20delicate%20Italian%20dishes%2C%20lasagna%20actually%20freezes%20and%20reheats%20very%20well%20%E2%80%94%20so%20don't%20be%20shy%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-know-if-leftovers-are-bad-2019-1%5C%22%3Etaking%20home%20leftovers%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20enjoying%20them%20the%20next%20day.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDon't%20overlook%20handmade%20pasta.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221069%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tagliatelle%20with%20seafood%20on%20plate%20at%20restaurant%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e85409cfb7f307e571eb2b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22802%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPasta%20is%20often%20one%20of%20the%20cheapest%20items%20in%20the%20grocery%20store%2C%20but%20it%20tastes%20different%20when%20it's%20made%20by%20hand.%3Cp%3EGu%20Studio%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EChef%20and%20restaurant%20consultant%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthejuliakitchen.com%2F%5C%22%3EJulia%20Helton%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20BI%20that%20when%20you're%20at%20an%20Italian%20eatery%20where%20chefs%20make%20their%20own%20pasta%2C%20you%20should%20always%20try%20to%20sample%20some.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20possible%20to%20make%20your%20own%20pasta%2C%20but%20doing%20it%20regularly%20is%20a%20hassle.%20Nicer%20Italian%20restaurants%20have%20a%20person%20on%20staff%20who%20only%20makes%20pasta.%20There%20is%20nothing%20like%20freshly%20made%20pasta%20%E2%80%94%20it%20makes%20going%20back%20to%20the%20dried%20stuff%20really%20difficult%2C%26quot%3B%20Helton%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20way%20to%20appreciate%20handmade%20pasta%2C%20which%20is%20often%20made%20daily%20with%20real%20eggs%2C%20is%20to%20order%20it%20with%20a%20sauce%20that%20enhances%20rather%20than%20conceals%20its%20natural%20flavor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20you%20might%20want%20to%20pair%20it%20with%20a%20light%20drizzle%20of%20olive%20oil%20or%20a%20thin%20tomato%20sauce%20rather%20than%20a%20heavy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhich-alfredo-sauce-should-i-buy-at-grocery-store-review-photos-2022%5C%22%3EAlfredo%20sauce%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EOrdering%20a%20braised%20dish%20is%20a%20smart%20way%20to%20spend%20your%20money.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224608%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22pasta%20with%20meat%20sugo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e15e57849878c33161cb534%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223456%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlthough%20much%20of%20Italian%20cuisine%20can%20be%20easy%20to%20whip%20up%20at%20home%2C%20some%20meals%20are%20a%20bit%20more%20labor-intensive.%3Cp%3EShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESecond-generation%20Italian%20chef%20Natale%20Servino%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.servino.com%2F%5C%22%3EServino%20Ristorante%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Tiburon%2C%20California%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20ordering%20a%20braised%20dish%20is%20a%20wise%20option%20because%20they%20are%20often%20quite%20labor-intensive%20to%20make.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBraising%20involves%20patiently%20searing%20or%20frying%20food%20in%20a%20pan%20at%20a%20high%20temperature%20before%20cooking%20it%20on%20low%20heat%20in%20a%20covered%20dish%20with%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20liquid.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBraised%20dishes%20can%20take%20up%20to%2012%20hours%20to%20create.%20I%20will%20always%20order%20a%20meat%20sugo%20with%20a%20pasta%20or%20braised%20meats%20when%20dining%20out%2C%20as%20it's%20a%20way%20to%20enjoy%20the%20taste%20of%20braised%20items%20without%20the%20labor%20of%20making%20them%20yourself%2C%26quot%3B%20Servino%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EVeal%20dishes%20like%20osso%20buco%20are%20usually%20worth%20the%20extra%20money.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22veal%2C%20onion%2C%20and%20carrot%20in%20a%20dark%20sauce%20in%20white%20tray%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e854aabf0250c21493b7cb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22864%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOsso%20buco%20can%20be%20challenging%20to%20make%20at%20home.%3Cp%3ERebeca%20Mello%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EChef%20and%20food%20blogger%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bitesizedkitchen.com%2F%5C%22%3E%20Aleka%20Shunk%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20dishes%20that%20involve%20veal%2C%20like%20osso%20buco%2C%20are%20often%20easier%20to%20sample%20in%20a%20restaurant%20setting%20than%20to%20make%20from%20scratch.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20love%20ordering%20osso%20buco%20because%20veal%20shanks%20are%20hard%20to%20find%20in%20many%20local%20food%20stores.%20Plus%2C%20this%20dish%20takes%20hours%20to%20make%20and%20I%20often%20don't%20have%20the%20time%20to%20spend%20cooking%20it%20at%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20Shunk%20told%20BI.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESomewhat%20similar%20dishes%20like%20veal%20Marsala%2C%20veal%20piccata%2C%20and%20veal%20scallopini%20with%20mushrooms%20are%20also%20tasty%20options%20that%20would%20be%20time-consuming%20to%20create%20from%20scratch%2C%20but%20usually%20earn%20their%20lofty%20restaurant%20price%20tags.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EArancini%20are%20a%20deep-fried%20Italian%20comfort%20food.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Three%20rice%20balls%20on%20rectangular%20plate%20topped%20with%20green%20herbs%20and%20on%20top%20of%20red%20sauce%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e856b5d17aa3c7b2b2fc74%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERice%20balls%20sometimes%20contain%20meat.%3Cp%3EThurtell%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20dish%20I%20love%20to%20order%20at%20Italian%20restaurants%20is%20arancini.%20They%20are%20very%20time-consuming%20to%20make%20at%20home%20and%20involve%20frying%2C%20which%20I%20try%20not%20to%20do%20often.%20However%2C%20I%20just%20love%20them%20so%20I%20treat%20myself%20when%20I%20am%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Shunk%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWarm%2C%20savory%2C%20and%20often%20bite-sized%2C%20arancini%20are%20small%20rice%20balls%20that%20are%20typically%20stuffed%20with%20tasty%20morsels%20like%20cheese%2C%20peas%2C%20or%20rag%C3%BA%20(a%20meat-based%20sauce).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20balls%20are%20then%20breaded%20and%20fried%20before%20being%20served%20hot%2C%20either%20alone%20or%20paired%20with%20a%20dipping%20sauce.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20meat%20is%20a%20traditional%20arancini%20filling%2C%20many%20restaurants%20offer%20vegetarian%20versions%20that%20are%20just%20as%20tasty.%20And%20if%20you%20want%20an%20authentic%20Italian%20flavor%2C%20try%20to%20stick%20with%20fillings%20like%20caciocavallo%20cheese%2C%20mozzarella%2C%20al%20burro%2C%20besciamella%2C%20rag%C3%BA%2C%20or%20al%20sugo.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Margherita%20pizza%20is%20often%20way%20overpriced%20for%20what%20it%20is.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221067%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Margherita%20Pizza%2C%20named%20after%20an%20Italian%20queen%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F59c008e252d8fb45008b4988%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMargherita%20pizza%20is%20made%20with%20fresh%20mozzarella%2C%20tomatoes%2C%20and%20basil.%3Cp%3EPixabay%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20imagine%20that%20pizza%20could%20ever%20be%20a%20bad%20choice%2C%20but%20Helton%20told%20BI%20that%20Margherita%20pies%20are%20%26quot%3Ba%20total%20rip-off%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20are%20often%20one%20of%20the%20most%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchefs-reveal-the-things-they-wish-diners-knew%5C%22%3Eoverpriced%20items%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20any%20restaurant%20menu.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStop%20paying%20for%20this%20dish%2C%26quot%3B%20Helton%20said.%20It's%20just%20dough%2C%20a%20little%20sauce%2C%20a%20few%20pieces%20of%20basil%2C%20and%20part%20of%20a%20log%20of%20mozzarella.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20paying%20%2412%20minimum%20for%20a%20dish%20that%20costs%20%241%20to%20make%2C%26quot%3B%20Helton%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20because%20I%20was%20the%20executive%20chef%20at%20an%20Italian%20restaurant%20for%20three%20years%2C%20so%20I%20worked%20out%20the%20cost%20many%20times%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20truly%20want%20a%20slice%20of%20pizza%20that's%20worth%20its%20price%20tag%2C%20spring%20for%20a%20flavor%20that%20incorporates%20a%20few%20different%20toppings%20or%20is%20explicated%20listed%20as%20%26quot%3Bwood-fired.%26quot%3B%20These%20factors%20can%20elevate%20a%20pizza%20beyond%20what%20you%20could%20easily%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fhomemade-pizza%5C%22%3Ewhip%20up%20at%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20few%20bucks.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EUnless%20tomatoes%20are%20in%20season%2C%20skip%20the%20caprese%20salad.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221595%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22caprese%20salad%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ee3d2025af6cc2b042e8513%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221196%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECaprese%20salad%20probably%20won't%20be%20very%20good%20if%20the%20tomatoes%20aren't%20in%20season.%3Cp%3EMediaNews%20Group%2FBay%20Area%20News%20via%20Getty%20Images%2FContributor%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECaprese%20salad%20is%20composed%20of%20thick%20slices%20of%20raw%20tomato%20and%20mozzarella%2C%20topped%20with%20fresh%20basil%20leaves%20and%20a%20splash%20of%20olive%20oil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20dish%20that%20really%20relies%20on%20the%20natural%20flavor%20of%20its%20few%20ingredients%2C%20which%20means%20that%20this%20salad%20can%20easily%20disappoint%20if%20not%20ordered%20at%20the%20right%20time%20of%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCaprese%20salad%20is%20a%20dish%20that%20you%20will%20find%20on%20a%20menu%20at%20an%20Italian%20restaurant%20year-round%2C%20as%20it%20is%20always%20a%20great%20seller%2C%26quot%3B%20Servino%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20more%20often%20than%20not%2C%20the%20tomatoes%20will%20be%20out%20of%20season%20and%20lack%20flavor.%20Only%20order%20this%20dish%20if%20tomatoes%20are%20in%20season.%20Otherwise%2C%20skip%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPass%20on%20the%20garlic%20bread%20unless%20it%20is%20served%20in%20a%20traditional%20style.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Garlic%20Bread%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5abd03a432167425008b4622%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221050%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGarlic%20lovers%20may%20struggle%20not%20to%20order%20a%20basket%20of%20garlic%20bread%2C%20but%20this%20is%20one%20side%20dish%20that's%20perhaps%20best%20prepared%20in%20your%20own%20kitchen.%3Cp%3ERichard%20Drew%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EServino%20told%20BI%20that%20shelling%20out%20top%20dollar%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhich-chef-has-the-best-recipe-for-garlic-bread%5C%22%3Egarlic%20bread%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20an%20Italian%20restaurant%20is%20usually%20a%20bad%20idea.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20restaurant%20has%20to%20hide%20the%20flavor%20of%20its%20bread%20with%20butter%20and%20garlic%2C%20you%20should%20probably%20skip%20it.%20Look%20for%20fresh%2C%20homemade%2C%20or%20locally%20made%20bread%20that%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20covered%20in%20butter%20and%20baked%20in%20order%20to%20taste%20good%2C%26quot%3B%20Servino%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20if%20you're%20outside%20Italy%20but%20want%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-authentic-italian-food-is-like-2018-3%5C%22%3Eauthentic%20dish%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20buttery%20garlic%20bread%20that's%20loaded%20with%20cheese%20shouldn't%20be%20a%20top%20choice.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Italy%2C%20bread%20is%20often%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-authentic-italian-food-is-like-2018-3%23simplicity-is-key-7%5C%22%3Eserved%20hot%20with%20roasted%20garlic%20and%20olive%20oil%3C%2Fa%3E.%20To%20get%20the%20aroma%20of%20the%20garlic%2C%20diners%20rub%20a%20crushed%20clove%20on%20the%20bread%20and%20then%20sparingly%20use%20oil%20to%20bring%20out%20the%20flavor.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESpaghetti%20Bolognese%20is%20another%20dish%20that%20is%20likely%20cheaper%20to%20make%20at%20home.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221014%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22SPAGHETTI%20BOLOGNESE%20PIXABAY%20RitaE%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5c86881ceb3ce80fe84bfbf3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22761%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOrdering%20it%20at%20a%20restaurant%20may%20be%20tasty%2C%20but%20isn't%20very%20economical.%3Cp%3EPixabay%2FRitaE%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-make-ina-garten-easy-weeknight-bolognese-pasta-2020-12%5C%22%3ESpaghetti%20Bolognese%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20quick%20to%20prepare%20at%20home%20and%20not%20very%20complicated%20to%20whip%20up.%20It%20is%20one%20of%20those%20dishes%20that%20is%20hard%20to%20mess%20up%20or%20overcook%20because%20the%20dish%20uses%20ground%20beef%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Shunk.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaking%20this%20Italian%20classic%20involves%20saut%C3%A9ing%20ground%20beef%20with%20minced%20gar