deral%20student-loan%20borrowers%20is%20coming%20to%20an%20end.%20Put%20in%20place%20last%20October%2C%20the%20Education%20Department%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-happens-if-i-miss-student-loan-payments-on-ramp-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eestablished%20a%2012-month%20period%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20which%20any%20missed%20payments%20would%20not%20be%20reported%20to%20credit%20agencies%2C%20giving%20borrowers%20some%20leeway%20if%20they%20could%20not%20afford%20payments%20or%20chose%20to%20skip%20them%20for%20any%20reason.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%2012-month%20on-ramp%20period%20protects%20borrowers%20from%20the%20worst%20consequences%20of%20missed%2C%20late%2C%20or%20partial%20payments%2C%20including%20negative%20credit%20reporting%20for%20delinquent%20payments%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20department%20wrote%20in%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstudentaid.gov%2Fmanage-loans%2Frepayment%2Fprepare-payments-restart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eguidance%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20department%20is%20not%20extending%20the%20on-ramp%2C%20meaning%20that%20in%20two%20weeks%2C%20borrowers%20who%20miss%20their%20payments%20will%20be%20marked%20as%20delinquent%20and%20reported%20to%20credit%20agencies%2C%20and%20their%20credit%20scores%20could%20take%20a%20hit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20missed%20payments%20typically%20wouldn't%20count%20toward%20forgiveness%20progress%20through%20programs%20like%20Public%20Service%20Loan%20Forgiveness%20and%20income-driven%20repayment%20plans%2C%20pushing%20back%20borrowers'%20timeline%20to%20see%20a%20full%20or%20partial%20reduction%20to%20their%20balances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20report%20from%20the%20Government%20Accountability%20Office%20found%20that%20just%2040%25%20of%20borrowers%20with%20payments%20greater%20than%20%240%20were%20current%20on%20their%20payments%20as%20of%20January%202024%2C%20likely%20reflecting%20borrowers'%20participation%20in%20the%20on-ramp%20period.%20Additionally%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbo.gov%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2F2024-09%2F58963-student-loan.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Congressional%20Budget%20Office%20found%20that%20in%20the%20years%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20pandemic%2C%20borrowers%20made%20payments%20greater%20than%20%2410%20in%20only%2038%25%20of%20the%20months%20in%20which%20they%20had%20a%20payment%20due%2C%20reflecting%20challenges%20in%20making%20payments%20before%20the%20on-ramp%20began.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20the%20on-ramp%20period%20ending%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdo-i-qualify-for-fresh-start-student-loan-debt-forgiveness-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Fresh%20Start%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20began%20in%202022%20to%20return%20over%207%20million%20borrowers%20in%20delinquency%20or%20default%20to%20good%20standing%20before%20they%20enter%20repayment%2C%20is%20also%20ending%20on%20September%2030.%20The%20New%20York%20Federal%20Reserve%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-fresh-start-plan-student-loan-debt-forgiveness-working-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%20the%20program%20worked%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20while%201.05%25%20of%20balances%20were%20more%20than%2090%20days%20delinquent%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202022%2C%20that%20declined%20to%200.94%25%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20program%20ending%20means%20that%20borrowers%20who%20fall%20into%20delinquency%20or%20default%20will%20not%20only%20take%20hits%20to%20their%20credit%20scores%2C%20but%20they%20could%20also%20suffer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-borrowers-lose-social-security-benefits-defaulted-payments-warren-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20consequences%20of%20missing%20payments%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20inclu