ations%20during%20lunch%20and%20coffee%20breaks%20at%20work%20to%20address%20the%20country's%20declining%20birth%20rate.%20The%20initiative%20comes%20as%20Russia's%20fertility%20rate%2C%20currently%20at%20about%201.5%20children%20per%20woman%2C%20falls%20significantly%20below%20the%202.1%20rate%20required%20to%20maintain%20a%20stable%20population%2C%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2C%20noindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmetro.co.uk%2F2024%2F09%2F15%2Fvladimir-putin-demands-russians-sex-work-fall-birth-rate-21608541%2F%5C%22%3EMetro%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%20Additionally%2C%20over%20a%20million%2C%20primarily%20younger%20Russians%2C%20have%20left%20the%20country%20amid%20the%20ongoing%20war%20with%20Ukraine%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHealth%20Minister%20Dr%20Yevgeny%20Shestopalov%20emphasised%20that%20being%20too%20busy%20at%20work%20is%20not%20a%20valid%20excuse%20for%20avoiding%20procreation.%20He%20suggested%20that%20people%20could%20take%20advantage%20of%20breaks%20to%20focus%20on%20expanding%20their%20families%2C%20noting%20that%20''life%20flies%20by%20too%20quickly.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20reporter%20asked%20him%20how%20people%20working%2012%20to%2014%20hours%20a%20day%20would%20find%20time%20to%20have%20children%2C%20he%20responded%20by%20suggesting%20they%20could%20use%20their%20break%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPreviously%2C%20Putin%20has%20insisted%2C%20''The%20preservation%20of%20the%20Russian%20people%20is%20our%20highest%20national%20priority.%20The%20fate%20of%20Russia....depends%20on%20how%20many%20of%20us%20there%20will%20be.%20It%20is%20a%20question%20of%20national%20importance.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20Russia's%20birth%20rate%20has%20hit%20its%20lowest%20point%20since%201999%2C%20with%20the%20number%20of%20live%20births%20in%20June%20falling%20below%20100%2C000.%20This%20drastic%20drop%20has%20raised%20concerns%20in%20Moscow%20about%20a%20severe%20population%20decline.%20According%20to%20Rosstat%2C%20Russia's%20governmental%20statistics%20agency%2C%20the%20country%20has%20seen%20a%20significant%20decrease%20in%20births%2C%20with%2016%2C000%20fewer%20children%20born%20between%20January%20and%20June%202024%20compared%20to%20the%20same%20period%20last%20year%2C%20as%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.euronews.com%2F2024%2F09%2F10%2Frussias-birth-rate-drops-to-its-lowest-in-a-quarter-century-data-shows%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEuro%20News%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20decline%20is%20further%20exacerbated%20by%20an%2018%25%20increase%20in%20population%20decline%2C%20with%2049%2C000%20more%20deaths%20recorded%20in%202024%20than%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20likely%20due%20to%20the%20ongoing%20conflict%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kremlin's%20efforts%20to%20boost%20Russia's%20declining%20birth%20rate%20have%20led%20to%20a%20series%20of%20measures%2C%20including%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFree%20fertility%20checks%3A%20Women%20in%20Moscow%2C%20aged%2018-40%2C%20are%20encouraged%20to%20undergo%20free%20fertility%20assessments%20to%20evaluate%20their%20%26quot%3Breproductive%20potential%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EEmployer%20coercion%3A%20MP%20Tatyana%20Butskaya%20has%20proposed%20a%20plan%20to%20pressure%20employers%20into%20encouraging%20their%20female%20employees%20to%20have%20children.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIncentives%3A%C2%A0Chelyabinsk%20region%20is%20offering%C2%A08%2C500%20pounds%C2%A0to%20female%20students%20under%2024%20for%20their%20first%20child's%20birth%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ERestricting%20abortion%3A%20Access%20to%20abortion%20across%20the%20country%20is%20being%20blocked%20as%20public%20figures%20and%20churchmen%20claim%20women's%20duty%20is%20to%20give%20birth%20and%20raise%20children.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EDivorce%20fees%3A%C2%A0Fees%20for%20divorce%20have%20been%20increased%20to%20discourage%20separation.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolitician%20Anna%20Kuznetsova%20has%20also%20demanded%20women%20start%20giving%20birth%20at%20a%20young%20age.%20She%20said%3A%20''You%20should%20start%20giving%20birth%20at%2019-20%20years%20old.%20Then%2C%20statistically%2C%20the%20family%20will%20be%20able%20to%20have%20three%2C%20four%2C%20or%20more%20children.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20critics%20argue%20these%20policies%20undermine%20individual%20autonomy%2C%20particularly%20for%20women%2C%20and%20may%20have%20unintended%20consequences%20on%20Russia's%20social%20fabric.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726489560000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Fetden2mo_vladimir-putin_625x300_13_August_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frussians-urged-to-have-sex-during-work-breaks-amid-countrys-declining-birth-rate-6578255%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20initiative%20comes%20as%20Russia's%20fertility%20rate%2C%20currently%20at%20about%201.5%20children%20per%20woman%2C%20falls%20significantly%20below%20the%202.1%20rate%20required%20to%20maintain%20a%20stable%20population.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frussians-urged-to-have-sex-during-work-breaks-amid-countrys-declining-birth-rate-6578255%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Trajectory%20is%20clear'%3A%20Israeli%20defense%20minister%20signals%20declining%20hope%20for%20peaceful%20resolution%20with%20Hezbollah%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726489484000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-113397081%2Cimgsize-1022918.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Ftrajectory-is-clear-israeli-defense-minister-signals-declining-hope-for-peaceful-resolution-with-hezbollah%2Farticleshow%2F113397054.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.c