20thanks%20to%20an%20invisible%20network%20of%20underground%20aquifers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20aquifers%20are%20essentially%20natural%20underground%20reservoirs%20formed%20in%20the%20porous%20layers%20of%20rock%20and%20sediment%20beneath%20Leh.%20They%20are%20recharged%20primarily%20by%20snowmelt%20from%20surrounding%20mountains%2C%20glacial%20melt%20from%20nearby%20glaciers%2C%20limited%20annual%20rainfall%2C%20and%20infiltration%20from%20rivers%20and%20streams.%20This%20recharge%20process%20is%20heavily%20influenced%20by%20seasonal%20patterns%2C%20with%20most%20occurring%20during%20the%20warmer%20months%20when%20snow%20and%20glaciers%20melt%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Dr%20Chorol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20aquifers%20act%20as%20a%20natural%20storage%20and%20filtration%20system%2C%20holding%20water%20that%20percolates%20through%20the%20ground%20and%20releasing%20it%20slowly%20over%20time.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20groundwater%20maintains%20a%20relatively%20stable%20temperature%2C%20which%20can%20be%20beneficial%20for%20both%20ecosystems%20and%20human%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20920px)%20100vw%2C%20920px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-1-1726233591.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Leh's%20groundwater%20gets%20recharged%20by%20snowmelt%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-1-1726233591.jpg%20920w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-1-1726233591-300x161.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-1-1726233591-500x268.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-1-1726233591-768x412.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-1-1726233591-150x81.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-365887%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22494%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ELeh%E2%80%99s%20underground%20network%20of%20aquifers%20is%20recharged%20by%20snowmelt%20and%20glacial%20melt.%20(Image%20courtesy%3A%20Reach%20Ladakh)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20way%20these%20aquifers%20support%20Leh%E2%80%99s%20thriving%20is%20multifaceted.%20They%20sustain%20natural%20vegetation%20crucial%20for%20the%20local%20ecosystem%20and%20enable%20agriculture%20in%20an%20otherwise%20arid%20environment.%20For%20human%20use%2C%20they%20feed%20springs%20used%20for%20drinking%20water%2C%20supply%20water%20for%20wells%2C%20and%20support%20traditional%20water%20management%20systems%20like%20%3Cem%3Ezings%3C%2Fem%3E%20(ponds)%20and%20%3Cem%3Eyura%3C%2Fem%3E%20(channels)%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20stored%20water%20in%20aquifers%20helps%20Leh%20withstand%20periods%20of%20low%20precipitation%2C%20providing%20resilience%20against%20drought.%20This%20consistent%20water%20supply%20allows%20for%20urban%20development%20and%20supports%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F282723%2Fbest-homestays-in-ladakh-things-to-do-in-leh-local-experience%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrowing%20tourism%20%3C%2Fa%3Eindustry%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnderstanding%20and%20properly%20managing%20this%20invisible%20network%20of%20aquifers%20is%20crucial%20for%20Leh%E2%80%99s%20sustainable%20future%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20face%20of%20climate%20change%20and%20increasing%20water%20demands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20crucial%20lifeline%20is%20under%20severe%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Slowly%20poisoning%20the%20very%20veins%20that%20sustain%20us%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20rising%20tourist%20footfall%2C%20unplanned%20development%20and%20poor%20water%20management%20practices%2C%20Dr%20Chorol%E2%80%99s%20nearly%20seven-year%20research%20into%20Leh%E2%80%99s%20groundwater%20has%20come%20up%20with%20some%20troubling%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDecline%20in%20water%20quality%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%E2%80%9COver%20the%20past%20six%20years%2C%20we%E2%80%99ve%20observed%20a%20significant%20decrease%20in%20water%20quality.%20For%20instance%2C%20Total%20Dissolved%20Solids%20(TDS)%20levels%20have%20increased%20by%20about%2030%25%20in%20some%20areas%2C%20from%20an%20average%20of%20300%20mg%2FL%20to%20over%20400%20mg%2FL.%20This%20rapid%20increase%20is%20alarming.%20To%20give%20you%20an%20idea%20of%20how%20serious%20the%20problem%20is%2C%20let%20me%20share%20some%20of%20our%20key%20findings%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20drinking%20water%2C%20we%20found%20that%203.57%25%20of%20our%20samples%20were%20of%20extremely%20poor%20quality%2C%20and%20another%203.57%25%20were%20poor.%20What%E2%80%99s%20particularly%20concerning%20is%20that%2092.86%25%20were%20only%20of%20average%20quality%2C%20and%20we%20didn%E2%80%99t%20find%20any%20samples%20in%20the%20good%20or%20excellent%20categories%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNitrate%20levels%20have%20risen%20by%20up%20to%2050%25%20in%20certain%20wells%2C%20approaching%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20(WHO)%20limit%20of%2050%20mg%2FL%20in%20some%20cases.%20We%E2%80%99ve%20also%20detected%20increasing%20concentrations%20of%20heavy%20metals%20like%20chromium%20and%20cadmium%20with%20some%20samples%20showing%20levels%20two%20to%20three%20times%20higher%20than%20what%20we%20observed%20six%20years%20ago.%20For%20irrigation%20water%2C%20the%20situation%20is%20equally%20worrying.%20We%20found%20that%203.57%25%20of%20samples%20were%20very%20poor%2C%2042.86%25%20were%20poor%2C%20and%2053.57%25%20were%20average.%20This%20indicates%20a%20widespread%20issue%20with%20water%20quality%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChange%20in%20groundwater%20chemistry%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20chemical%20composition%20of%20Leh%E2%80%99s%20groundwater%20has%20altered%20noticeably.%20%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99re%20seeing%20increased%20levels%20of%20ions%20like%20chloride%2C%20sulphate%2C%20and%20sodium%2C%20which%20are%20typically%20associated%20with%20human%20activities.%20For%20example%2C%20chloride%20concentrations%20have%20risen%20by%20about%2040%25%20in%20some%20wells%20over%20the%20six%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20change%20suggests%20contamination%20from%20sources%20like%20improper%20sewage%20disposal%20and%20the%20concentration%20of%20major%20cations%20has%20increased%2C%20following%20the%20order%20of%20calcium%2C%20magnesium%2C%20sodium%2C%20and%20potassium.%20We%E2%80%99re%20seeing%20higher%20levels%20of%20sodium%2C%20potassium%2C%20fluoride%2C%20and%20nitrates%2C%20which%20we%20believe%20are%20linked%20to%20the%20increased%20use%20of%20agrochemicals%20in%20agriculture%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20particularly%20concerning%20is%20the%20elevated%20levels%20of%20heavy%20metals%20we%E2%80%99re%20detecting.%20Iron%2C%20manganese%2C%20chromium%2C%20nickel%2C%20cadmium%2C%20and%20copper%20are%20all%20present%20at%20levels%20exceeding%20permissible%20limits%20in%20many%20of%20the%20samples%20studied%20by%20Dr%20Chorol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99re%20seeing%20contamination%20from%20various%20sources%20%E2%80%94%20sewage%20leaking%20from%20poorly%20maintained%20septic%20systems%2C%20agricultural%20runoff%20from%20fertilisers%2C%20waste%20from%20increased%20tourism%2C%20and%20lack%20of%20proper%20wastewater%20treatment%20facilities.%20Each%20of%20these%20sources%20might%20seem%20small%20on%20its%20own%20but%20together%2C%20they%E2%80%99re%20having%20a%20significant%20impact%20on%20our%20water%20quality.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20complex%20issue%2C%20but%20understanding%20it%20is%20the%20first%20step%20towards%20addressing%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-5-1726233757.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Leh%20groundwater%20is%20suffering%20due%20to%20poor%20sewage%20management%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-5-1726233757.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-5-1726233757-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-5-1726233757-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-5-1726233757-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-5-1726233757-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-365888%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EA%20sewer%20cleaning%20truck%20in%20Leh%3A%20Sewage%20management%20is%20a%20serious%20problem%20in%20this%20high-altitude%20town%20(Image%20courtesy%20Shutterstock%2F%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.shutterstock.com%2Fg%2FOliverFoerstner%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOliver%20Foerstner%3C%2Fa%3E)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHealth%20risks%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%E2%80%9CFirstly%2C%20we%20found%20that%20certain%20heavy%20metals%2C%20such%20as%20chromium%2C%20cadmium%2C%20and%20nickel%2C%20present%20in%20the%20groundwater%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20increase%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noo